result.execSummary:
The defendant Bernard Lee Jackson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

May be released as early as 2 years if probation agent approves and all requirements are completed.

Comply with any conditions per agent.

Complete any programming and treatment deemed appropriate by agent.

No contact with anyone involved in the use, sale, possession or manufacturing of illegal drugs.

No contact with A.H.

No consumption or possession of alcohol and no entering taverns, bars or liquor stores for any purpose except as approved by agent.

No possession of prescription drugs not prescribed to defendant.

Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

DEFENDANT ENTITLED TO 3 DAYS SENTENCE CREDIT IF PROBATION IS REVOKED.
